  "comments": "<p>Exists two main variants of this coin :<br><strong><u>TYPE 1</u></strong>: Reverse legend: DAN:NO:V:G:Q:REX:(date)(mm) Value as XVI/E REIS/DAL<br><strong><u>TYPE 2</u></strong>: Reverse legend: MON:NOV:GLUCKSTADT:(date)(mm) Value as XVI/E REIC/HS DA<br>There are also two Obverse legends:</p><p>Legend 1: CHRISTI.4.D:G:D.N:V:G:Q:R<br>Legend 2: CHRISTIANVS·IIII·D:G<br><br>exemple of 1641 coin with obverse legend 1<br><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/5c03c7fc36536.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/5c03c7fc36536.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a><br><br>exemple of 1643 with dotted border on obverse<br><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/5c03ca44007ac.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/5c03ca44007ac.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a><br><br>exemple of coin of 1646 with different bust style<br><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/5c03cc7dd8a3d.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/5c03cc7dd8a3d.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a><br><br>Mintmarks:<br>(f) = monogram with feather and ST letters<br>(h) = crossed halberds</p>",
